kiosk

Class Kiosk

  • java.lang.Object
    • kiosk.Kiosk

  • public class Kiosk
extends java.lang.Object
    The Kiosk class is what enables users to schedule their appointment by writing in a specific format. It knows what are errors or bad commands given to it as well as it knows all the valid commands it needs to know to run. Capable to run, add, remove, print, and stop the scheduling process.
    Author:
    Jah C. Speed, Abe Vitangcol

        Returns:

      • checkValidBDate

        private boolean checkValidBDate(Date date)

        Parameters:

        false if the dob is not a valid dob (in the future / not a date), true otherwise.

      • doCommand

        private void doCommand(int command,
                       Patient patient,
                       Timeslot time,
                       Location local)
        Performs a command that requires parameters to execute. Will add or remove appointments based on the command given.
        Parameters:
        command - The identification code of the command based on the enum class. patient The patient looking for an appointment. time The timeslot of the appointment wanted. local The location of the appointment booked.

      • doNoNameCommand

        private int doNoNameCommand(int command)
        Performs a command that requires no further parameters. Will print the array with specifications based on the command, end the kiosk, or state the invalidity of the command.
        Parameters:
        command - The identification code of the command based on the enum class.
        Returns:
        0 if a print or invalid branch has been reached successfully, -1 otherwise.
